{
    "id": "12",
    "title": "Donor Lymphocyte Infusion (DLI) Volume",
    "desc": "The Donor Lymphocyte Infusion (DLI) Volume to Process by Apheresis estimates the volume of whole blood to be processed by apheresis to yield an appropriate DLI dosage.",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://www.google.com/books/edition/Hematopoietic_Stem_Cell_Transplantation/wzkNYAAACAAJ?hl=en",
                "text": "Wingard JR. Hematopoietic Stem Cell Transplantation, A Handbook for Clinicians. 2010."
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [],
        "evidence": "<p></p>\n<p>(A) Absolute CD3<sup>+</sup> lymphocyte count, cells/mL = donor WBC x donor % total lymphocytes x donor % CD3+ lymphocytes x 1,000</p>\n<p>(B) Total CD3+ cells needed = weight, kg x CD3<sup>+</sup> infusion dose, cells/kg x number of doses desired</p>\n<p>(C) Total blood volume needed, L = (B / A) / collection efficiency</p>\n<p>Note: percents should be expressed as fractions, e.g. 30% total lymphocytes should be 0.30 in equation (A).</p>\n<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n<p>For a 85 kg patient with WBC 6.2, 30% lymphocytes, 54% CD3<sup><sub>+</sub></sup> lymphocytes who will receive 2 doses of 50 &times; 10⁶ cells/kg each, collection efficiency 50%:</p>\n<p>(A) Absolute CD3<sup>+</sup>&nbsp;lymphocyte count = 6.2 x 10<sup>3</sup> x 0.30 x 0.54 x 1,000 = 1.004 x 10<sup>6</sup> cells/mL</p>\n<p>(B) Total CD3<sup>+</sup> cells needed = 85 x (50&nbsp;&times; 10⁶) x 2 = 8.5 x 10<sup>9</sup> CD3<sup>+</sup> cells</p>\n<p>(C) Total blood volume needed, L = 8.5 x 10<sup>9</sup> / 1.004 x 10<sup>6</sup> / 0.5 = 16.9 L</p>",
